<br>
I got my first KEI as a newbie at level 8... MGB'd in rivervale.  I went fishing, and thought my mana bar was broken because it wasn't going down as I was practicing my root/nuke on myself... hehe.<br>
<br>
Other than that one time, the first time I got it and knew what it was I was level 30, and it is like turning God mode on at that level.<br>
<br>
It makes you just like the guy in this post, Mr. Wheeler vs. Mr. Walker for anyone who ever watched that.  You want more more more mobs to kill, because you have enough mana to handle anything, you're the king of the world.<br>
<br>
My guess would be the rest of the group needed to med a bit, maybe the cleric, and you were screaming at them to pull more mobs, maybe more politely.  I'd imagine the group leader, being prudent and wanting the cleric to have mana, asked you to chill and &quot;tone it down&quot;.<br>
<br>
-----------------<br>
<br>
I think MGB and Group buffs shouldn't land on people under the level the spell is intended for, for KEI I think that is 45.  I am no hypocrite either, I thought that within half an hour of first getting it at level 30.  I posted about it at level 40, I don't think it would be that hard to fix.  Same with Ageo etc. simply should ignore the people under lvl 45 when MGB'd or Group cast.<br>
<br>
